SIMPLE: double-tongued
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Double-tongued
<hw>Dou"ble-tongued`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Making
contrary declarations on the same subject; deceitful.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> deceitful, double-faced, hypocritical, Janus-faced,
two-faced.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Likewise must the deacons be grave, not
<qex>double-tongued</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>1 Tim. iii. 8.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Double-tonguing</ent>⟦br⟧
